The evidence with the title 'Just 62 people now own the same wealth as half the world's ... ' says Jan 17, 2016  ... Wealth inequality has grown to the stage where 62 of the world 's richest people own as much as the poorest half of humanity combined , according to a new report . The research, conducted by the charity Oxfam, found that the wealth of the poorest half of the world 's population – 3.6 billion people – has fallen  ... 
